text: create a PLpgSQL procedure to increase each Sales value in journal by para_Sales.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Sales integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE "journal" SET "Sales" = "Sales" + para_Sales; END; $$;
skeleton: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(_ _) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE _ SET _ = _ + _; END; $$;

plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Last_year text, para_Party_ID integer, para_Location text) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE "party" SET "Last_year" = para_Last_year WHERE "Party_ID" = para_Party_ID or "Location" = para_Location; END; $$;

text: create a stored procedure in PLpgSQL to update Oppose_rate to para_Oppose_rate * para_Oppose_rate - 1 and People_ID to para_People_ID in candiinteger, then delete rows where Candiinteger_ID is para_Candiinteger_ID + 1.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Oppose_rate real, para_People_ID integer, para_Candiinteger_ID integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE "candiinteger" SET "Oppose_rate" = para_Oppose_rate * para_Oppose_rate - 1, "People_ID" = para_People_ID; DELETE FROM "candiinteger" WHERE "Candiinteger_ID" = para_Candiinteger_ID + 1; END; $$;
skeleton: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(_ _, _ _, _ _) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE _ SET _ = _ * _ - 1, _ = _; DELETE FROM _ WHERE _ = _ + 1; END; $$;

text: write a stored procedure in PLpgSQL, if para_Driver_ID is greater than 30, then insert a new record into driver table setting Driver_ID to para_Driver_ID and Home_city to para_Home_city.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Driver_ID integer, para_Home_city text) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN IF para_Driver_ID > 30 THEN INSERT INTO "driver" ("Driver_ID", "Home_city") VALUES (para_Driver_ID, para_Home_city); END IF; END; $$;
skeleton: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(_ _, _ _) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN IF _ > 30 THEN INSERT INTO _ (_, _) VALUES (_, _); END IF; END; $$;

text: write a stored procedure in PLpgSQL, in the People_Addresses table, update the integer_from column value to para_integer_from for the rows whose integer_to value is para_integer_to and person_address_id value is less than para_person_address_id.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_integer_from text, para_integer_to text, para_person_address_id integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE "People_Addresses" SET "integer_from" = para_integer_from WHERE "integer_to" = para_integer_to and "person_address_id" < para_person_address_id; END; $$;

text: Create a PLpgSQL function to remove rows from player matching Team = para_Team, School_ID = para_School_ID, and Player_ID = para_Player_ID, followed by updating all rows' Player columns to para_Player.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Team text, para_School_ID integer, para_Player_ID integer, para_Player text) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN DELETE FROM "player" WHERE "Team" = para_Team AND "School_ID" = para_School_ID AND "Player_ID" = para_Player_ID; IF FOUND THEN UPDATE "player" SET "Player" = para_Player; END IF; END; $$;
